name: taskqueue
title: TaskQueue API
description: Accesses a Google App Engine Pull Task Queue over REST.

parameters.name: userIp
parameters.desc: IP address of the site where the request originates. Use this if you want to enforce per-user limits.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters. Overrides userIp if both are provided.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The kind of object returned, a list of tasks.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The actual list of tasks currently active in the TaskQueue.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The kind of object returned, in this case set to task.

fields.name: leaseTimestamp
fields.desc: Time (in seconds since the epoch) at which the task lease will expire. This value is 0 if the task isnt currently leased out to a worker.

fields.name: payloadBase64
fields.desc: A bag of bytes which is the task payload. The payload on the JSON side is always Base64 encoded.

fields.name: queueName
fields.desc: Name of the queue that the task is in.

fields.name: enqueueTimestamp
fields.desc: Time (in seconds since the epoch) at which the task was enqueued.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Name of the task.

fields.name: stats
fields.desc: Statistics for the TaskQueue object in question.

fields.name: leasedLastHour
fields.desc: Number of tasks leased in the last hour.

fields.name: leasedLastMinute
fields.desc: Number of tasks leased in the last minute.

fields.name: oldestTask
fields.desc: The timestamp (in seconds since the epoch) of the oldest unfinished task.

fields.name: totalTasks
fields.desc: Number of tasks in the queue.

fields.name: acl
fields.desc: ACLs that are applicable to this TaskQueue object.

fields.name: adminEmails
fields.desc: Email addresses of users who are "admins" of the TaskQueue. This means they can control the queue, eg set ACLs for the queue.

fields.name: consumerEmails
fields.desc: Email addresses of users who can "consume" tasks from the TaskQueue. This means they can Dequeue and Delete tasks from the queue.

fields.name: producerEmails
fields.desc: Email addresses of users who can "produce" tasks into the TaskQueue. This means they can Insert tasks into the queue.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Name of the taskqueue.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The kind of REST object returned, in this case taskqueue.

fields.name: maxLeases
fields.desc: The number of times we should lease out tasks before giving up on them. If unset we lease them out forever until a worker deletes the task.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The actual list of tasks returned as a result of the lease operation.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The kind of object returned, a list of tasks.

methods.desc: Lease 1 or more tasks from a TaskQueue.

pathParams.desc: The project under which the queue lies.

pathParams.desc: The taskqueue to lease a task from.

requiredQueryParams.name: numTasks
requiredQueryParams.desc: The number of tasks to lease.
